<plot>A quirky, romantic comedy about the complexity and frustration of finding a true love in the gay community. Marc (Michael Shawn Lucas) is a struggling actor who finds an apartment in NYC by searching the obituaries. He lives with his out-of-work, eccentric fag-hag Cynthia (Mara Hobel). His best friend, Robert, is secretly in love with Marc, while Marc falls head over heels for flighty studio musician David (Hugh Panaro). Things heat up as Marc's desire for David keeps him waiting by the phone, while Cynthia gets financially cut off from her rich parents and Robert struggles to express his feelings for Marc.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?083674</url></doc>
